---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

---

<Layout title="About Us" description="Learn about Summer Willis Foundation — our story, mission, and the team dedicated to survivor advocacy and systemic change.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Sun.png" alt="" class="header-sun" aria-hidden="true" />
    <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Sun.png" alt="" class="sun-bl" aria-hidden="true" />
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Summer Willis Foundation</h1>
      <p>A survivor-centered organization built on advocacy, community, and lasting change.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tagline Banner -->
  <section class="tagline-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="tagline">Through trauma-informed advocacy, bipartisan collaboration, and transformative storytelling, we create spaces where survivors are empowered to share their experiences and drive systemic change.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Story -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-grid">
      <div class="story-text">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Story</h2>
        <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Underline.png" alt="" class="section-underline" aria-hidden="true" />
        <p>Our founder, Summer Willis, is a survivor of sexual violence. In the wake of her assault, she experienced firsthand the systemic failures, silence, and shame that often define the survivor experience. She began running as a bold act of reclamation. This personal challenge grew into <a href="https://www.glamour.co.za/lifestyle/motivation-monday-summer-willis-on-resilience-running-29-marathons-and-turning-pain-into-purpose-ee96ef85-5c85-424e-8968-77d37c3cbf5a" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #00909d;"><strong>'Project 29'</strong></a>— a commitment to run 29 marathons as a testament to her own resilience. She met survivors around the world, each with different lives yet she observed the same pattern. She realized Sexual violence thrives on shame, silence, and laws that haven't kept up with reality. Eventually, Project 29 grew into the Summer Willis Foundation. SWF was established to combat the root causes of sexual violence in innovative and community-driven ways to make a lasting impact.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-image">
        <div class="video-frame">
          <video
            class="story-video"
            controls
            preload="metadata"
            id="story-video"
          >
            <source src="/images/videos/summer_vid.mov" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story + Values Combined -->
  <section class="section story-values-section">
    <div class="container story-values-grid">

      <!-- Left: Extended Story -->
      <div class="story-extended">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">All About Our Story</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Running was only the start.</h2>
        <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Underline.png" alt="" class="section-underline" aria-hidden="true" />
        <p>Summer found her true, renewed strength not just in the miles, but in community, in the power of telling her story without shame , and in a fierce new purpose: creating tangible change so that what happened to her wouldn't happen to others. She realized she had a choice: accept the narrative of 'victim,' or rewrite it. She chose to rewrite it. That single run transformed into a public mission. What started as 'Project 29' became a movement. Summer founded the Summer Willis Foundation to ensure that no survivor ever feels alone and that every survivor has the tools to find their own power—whether on the running path, in their community, or in creating systemic change.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Card Stack -->
      <div class="card-stack-wrap">
        <p class="values-label">Mission &amp; Values</p>
        <p class="values-hint">Click to flip through</p>
        <div class="card-stack" id="values-stack">
          <div class="stack-card card-teal">
            <div class="stack-icon">🎯</div>
            <h3>Our Mission</h3>
            <p>Through our commitment to advocacy, community, and resource provision, the Summer Willis Foundation exists to reframe the narrative around sexual violence, empower survivors to reclaim their stories, and create lasting systemic change that prevents future harm.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stack-card card-yellow">
            <div class="stack-icon">💛</div>
            <h3>Believe Survivors</h3>
            <p>We center survivor voices in everything we do — leading with compassion, trust, and unconditional support.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stack-card card-pink">
            <div class="stack-icon">🤝</div>
            <h3>Community</h3>
            <p>Healing happens in community. We build brave, connected spaces where survivors are never alone.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stack-card card-blue">
            <div class="stack-icon">📣</div>
            <h3>Systemic Change</h3>
            <p>We don't just respond to harm — we work to dismantle the systems and cultures that allow it to persist.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tenets -->
  <section class="section tenets-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">How We Create Change</h2>
      <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Underline.png" alt="" class="section-underline" aria-hidden="true" />
      <p class="section-subtitle">Three core pillars drive everything we do — from the individual survivor to systems of power.</p>
      <div class="tenets-grid">

        <div class="tenet-card tenet-teal">
          <div class="tenet-number">01</div>
          <h3>Combatting Stigma and Shame</h3>
          <p>We're combatting shame and stigma by focusing on resilience, community, and strength. SWF understands that community and collective action can be transformative in ending stigma and empowering individuals to be their own change-makers. With this, we build a movement to end sexual violence. </p>
        </div>

        <div class="tenet-card tenet-yellow">
          <div class="tenet-number">02</div>
          <h3>Building Survivor-Led Communities</h3>
          <p>We foster local, national and global safe spaces where survivors and allies can connect, heal, and create lasting change together, through our Denim Race Series, speaking engagements, upcoming Resource Map and Advocacy Bootcamp projects, and more.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tenet-card tenet-pink">
          <div class="tenet-number">03</div>
          <h3>Fighting for Policy Reform</h3>
          <p>We work with legislators across party lines at the highest levels of government, both federally and at the state level,  to push for stronger protections and accountability for survivors.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Meet Our Team</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Dedicated advocates committed to survivors and systemic change every day.</p>

      <!-- Featured: Summer Willis -->
      <div class="founder-card founder-card--teal">
        <div class="founder-avatar founder-avatar--teal">👩</div>
        <div class="founder-info">
          <div class="founder-roles">
            <span class="founder-badge">Board President</span>
            <span class="founder-badge">Founder & Executive Director</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Summer Willis</h3>
          <p>Summer Willis is the Founder, Executive Director, and Board President of The Summer Willis Foundation. A Mom and Wife, her commitment to public service includes prior roles as a Teach for America educator and a Peace Corps Volunteer. Leveraging her personal journey, she became the namesake of the <strong>Summer Willis Act in Texas</strong>, which redefined consent law. She is an endurance athlete who sometimes takes on extreme challenges, such as running 29 marathons in a single year, to raise awareness and fund survivor resources.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Featured: Katiana Soenen -->
      <div class="founder-card founder-card--yellow">
        <div class="founder-avatar founder-avatar--yellow">👩</div>
        <div class="founder-info">
          <div class="founder-roles">
            <span class="founder-badge">Board Vice President</span>
            <span class="founder-badge">Chief Development Officer</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Katiana Soenen</h3>
          <p>Katiana is the Board Vice President and Chief Development Officer at the Summer Willis Foundation, where she leads national awareness campaigns, fundraising initiatives, and organizational expansion.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">After being sexually assaulted during her first year of college, Katiana found strength in advocacy. Her early activism began with serving as a named plaintiff in a <strong>Title IX compliance case</strong>, pressing for stronger campus-safety systems and institutional accountability. Before joining SWF, she focused on grassroots efforts to expand resources for college survivors as well as reproductive rights advocacy in Texas and Tennessee.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Alongside founder Summer Willis, Katiana now drives SWF's development pipeline, donor partnerships, multi-state growth, and high-impact national campaigns — including the forthcoming Denim Runs series, a national resource map for survivors, and the "Letter to My Younger Self" film. She is dedicated to building innovative and sustainable infrastructure, amplifying survivor voices, and advancing meaningful policy change.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.9rem;">Born and raised in Texas · B.A. Political Science & Public Health, Vanderbilt University · Certified Yoga Instructor</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Featured: Samantha McCoy -->
      <div class="founder-card founder-card--pink">
        <div class="founder-avatar founder-avatar--pink">👩</div>
        <div class="founder-info">
          <div class="founder-roles">
            <span class="founder-badge">Board Secretary</span>
            <span class="founder-badge">VP for Public Policy</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Samantha McCoy</h3>
          <p>Samantha McCoy is an award-winning appellate attorney, public speaker, activist, and licensed master social worker. Following a sexually violent crime, Samantha dedicated her career to ensuring all gaps within the judicial system are finally closed and all survivors of sexual violence are treated in a dignified and trauma-informed manner.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Samantha has successfully lobbied for several laws in five states, the <strong>federal TAKE IT DOWN Act</strong>, and a <strong>United Nations Resolution</strong> — all of which strengthened the rights and protections for survivors.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.9rem;">M.S.W. & Certificate of Advanced Study in Trauma-Informed Practice, Syracuse University · J.D. <em>summa cum laude</em>, St. Mary's University School of Law</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Advisory Board -->
  <section class="section advisory-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Advisory Board</h2>
      <img src="/images/icons/SWF - Underline.png" alt="" class="section-underline" aria-hidden="true" />
      <p class="section-subtitle">Experts, survivors, and advocates who guide our work with wisdom, lived experience, and specialized expertise.</p>

      <div class="advisory-grid">

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--teal">
          <div class="advisory-header">
            <div class="advisory-avatar advisory-avatar--teal">👩</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Kelly Joseph</h3>
              <span class="advisory-label advisory-label--teal">Founder, La Sœur Fund</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advisory-bio">
            <p>Kelly Shawn Joseph is a specialist in preventing and responding to violence against women and girls across humanitarian, development, and crisis-affected contexts — including Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Central African Republic, Iraq, Lebanon, Mali, Somalia, and Ukraine. Her work focuses on strengthening survivor-centered prevention and response systems in complex and politically constrained environments.</p>
            <p>She is the Founder of <strong>La Sœur Fund</strong>, a women's fund that directly resources grassroots women- and girl-led organizations responding to violence in emergencies through participatory grantmaking and trust-based, risk-aware approaches. In advisory roles, Kelly supports organizations to deepen technical rigor while remaining accountable to survivors, frontline practitioners, and feminist movements.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="advisory-read-more">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--yellow">
          <div class="advisory-header">
            <div class="advisory-avatar advisory-avatar--yellow">👩</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Kathryne Hemmings</h3>
              <span class="advisory-label advisory-label--yellow">Senior Counsel, Horn Williamson LLC</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advisory-bio">
            <p>Kathryne Hemmings is a survivor, an advocate, and an attorney committed to ensuring that those who experience sexual violence are met with dignity, belief, and meaningful support. Her connection to this work began long before her legal career. As an undergraduate at Clemson University, she survived a sexual assault that reshaped her life and her understanding of what it means to navigate trauma in environments that often feel unprepared—or unwilling—to help.</p>
            <p>That experience fuels her dedication to ensuring no survivor feels alone in the aftermath of harm. In her legal career, Kathryne has represented students who were assaulted at their universities, supporting them as they faced complex institutional processes and deeply personal challenges. Her work has always centered on listening closely, validating lived experiences, and advocating in ways that honor each survivor's agency and story.</p>
            <p>Beyond litigation, Kathryne is committed to community education, outreach, and opening pathways to healing—especially for those who feel silenced by stigma or discouraged by systems that have failed them. She believes strongly in strengthening survivor-support networks, expanding access to trauma-informed resources, and fostering environments where healing is not only possible but supported at every step.</p>
            <p>Kathryne joined the advisory board of Strength Through Strides because the organization's mission aligns with the heart of her life's work: creating compassionate, survivor-centered spaces where people can find support, connection, and empowerment. She is honored to help further the organization's vision and to stand alongside survivors as they reclaim their strength and their stories.</p>
            <p>Today, Kathryne serves as Senior Counsel at Horn Williamson, LLC in Philadelphia, where she represents homeowners and community members in complex civil matters. In her day-to-day work, she continues to prioritize clear communication, trust-building, and advocacy that centers the human beings behind every case—values that also guide her commitment to supporting survivors through Strength Through Strides.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="advisory-read-more">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--pink">
          <div class="advisory-header">
            <div class="advisory-avatar advisory-avatar--pink">👩</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Sophia-Rose Centurioni</h3>
              <span class="advisory-label advisory-label--pink">Dancer, Advocate & Survivor</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advisory-bio">
            <p>Sophia-Rose is a dancer, advocate, and survivor who uses her story to help others feel safe, seen, and supported. She was sexually assaulted at 16 — a trauma that brought fear, shame, and silence. Through therapy, education, and steady healing, she reclaimed her voice and learned that adversity does not define her.</p>
            <p>Today, she speaks openly so no young person feels alone in their recovery. Through her work with <strong>R.I.S.E.</strong> (Resilience, Inspiration, Support, Empowerment), she teaches teens about safety, boundaries, healthy relationships, and the power of healing. Her mission: help survivors stand stronger and help every young person know their worth.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="advisory-read-more">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--teal">
          <div class="advisory-header">
            <div class="advisory-avatar advisory-avatar--teal">👩</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Paulina Pizarro</h3>
              <span class="advisory-label advisory-label--teal">Nonprofit Management · 25+ Years</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advisory-bio">
            <p>Paulina has over 25 years of experience in nonprofit management, working and volunteering in arts management, education, and equity-based organizations. She has served on various nonprofit boards throughout her career.</p>
            <p style="color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 0.75rem;">Originally from Chile · B.A. Economics, Texas A&M University</p>
          </div>
          <button class="advisory-read-more">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--yellow">
          <div class="advisory-header">
            <div class="advisory-avatar advisory-avatar--yellow">👩</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Ashley Brooks</h3>
              <span class="advisory-label advisory-label--yellow">Senior Policy Advisor, TAASA</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advisory-bio">
            <p>Ashley Brooks currently serves as the Senior Policy Advisor for the Texas Association Against Sexual Assault (TAASA). She brings over 20 years of experience in public service to the Summer Willis Foundation Advisory Board.</p>
            <p style="color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 0.75rem;">Alumna, University of Texas at Austin</p>
          </div>
          <button class="advisory-read-more">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👩</div>
          <h3>Briana Ferrigno</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👩</div>
          <h3>Emily Carter</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👨</div>
          <h3>Drew Woodley</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👩</div>
          <h3>Dini Von Mueffling</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👩</div>
          <h3>Gabriella Taylor</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👨</div>
          <h3>Will Rivera</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="advisory-card advisory-card--compact">
          <div class="advisory-avatar">👩</div>
          <h3>Valeria Angyal</h3>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-strip">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div>
        <h2>Stand with survivors.</h2>
        <p>Advocates, allies, and donors make our work possible.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/get-involved" class="btn btn-primary">Get Involved</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .section-underline {
    height: 28px;
    width: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 1.25rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .page-header {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--c-primary-dark), var(--c-primary));
    color: white;
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .header-sun {
    position: absolute;
    top: -30px;
    right: -30px;
    width: 220px;
    height: auto;
    opacity: 0.12;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header p { font-size: 1.1rem; opacity: 0.9; margin: 0; }

  .tagline-section {
    background: var(--c-bg-yellow);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--c-yellow);
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tagline {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #374151;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--c-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  /* Combined Story + Values */
  .story-values-section { background: #f9fafb; }

  .story-values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .story-extended p {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Values Flip Cards */
  .values-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--c-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .values-hint {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #9ca3af;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  /* Card Stack */
  .card-stack-wrap { }

  .card-stack {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    perspective: 1000px;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .stack-card {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    border-radius: 16px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
    will-change: transform, box-shadow;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    will-change: transform;
  }

  .stack-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0;
    color: #111827;
  }

  .stack-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .stack-icon { font-size: 2rem; }

  .card-teal   { background: var(--c-bg-teal);   border: 2px solid rgba(0,144,157,0.25); }
  .card-yellow { background: var(--c-bg-yellow);  border: 2px solid rgba(255,198,11,0.35); }
  .card-pink   { background: var(--c-bg-pink);    border: 2px solid rgba(239,63,107,0.25); }
  .card-blue   { background: var(--c-bg-blue);    border: 2px solid rgba(100,160,220,0.25); }

  .story-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .story-text p {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .video-frame {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 8px;
    background: white;
    border: 3px solid var(--c-primary);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.12), 6px 6px 0 var(--c-yellow);
  }

  .story-video {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 14px;
    display: block;
  }


  /* Tenets */
  .tenets-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tenet-card {
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-top: 4px solid transparent;
  }

  .tenet-teal { background: var(--c-bg-teal); border-top-color: var(--c-primary); }
  .tenet-yellow { background: var(--c-bg-yellow); border-top-color: var(--c-yellow); }
  .tenet-pink { background: var(--c-bg-pink); border-top-color: var(--c-pink-dark); }

  .tenet-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'TAYBirdie', system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  .tenet-teal .tenet-number { color: var(--c-primary); }
  .tenet-yellow .tenet-number { color: #b08000; }
  .tenet-pink .tenet-number { color: var(--c-pink-dark); }

  .tenet-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    color: #111827;
  }

  .tenet-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .founder-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-left-width: 4px;
  }

  .founder-card--teal {
    background: var(--c-bg-teal);
    border-color: var(--c-blue-light);
    border-left-color: var(--c-primary);
  }

  .founder-card--yellow {
    background: var(--c-bg-yellow);
    border-color: var(--c-yellow-light);
    border-left-color: var(--c-yellow);
  }

  .founder-card--pink {
    background: var(--c-bg-pink);
    border-color: var(--c-pink);
    border-left-color: var(--c-pink-dark);
  }

  .founder-avatar {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    width: 88px;
    height: 88px;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    border: 2px solid var(--c-blue-light);
  }

  .founder-avatar--yellow { border-color: var(--c-yellow-light); }
  .founder-avatar--pink { border-color: var(--c-pink); }

  .founder-roles {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .founder-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--c-primary);
    color: white;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  .founder-card--yellow .founder-badge {
    background: var(--c-yellow);
    color: #111827;
  }

  .founder-card--pink .founder-badge {
    background: var(--c-pink-dark);
    color: white;
  }

  .founder-info h3 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
